libarc
------------------------------------------
Libarc is a C++ library for accessing the contents of GZIP compressed ARC
files generated by the Internet Archive's Heritrix web crawler. It provides
the following services:
 * Opening and scanning the contents of GZIP compressed ARC file. The
   library does not currently read CDX index files, though this feature will
   be added in a future release.
 * You can get an iterator to walk over the contents of the ARC file member by
   member. You can specify a media type to limit the types members you see.
 * You can access the information in the member's URL record and the response
   headers from the HTTP server.
 * You can access the member's data in a single API call.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.7.35-1
  libarc-devel-0.2.0-1bl2
  libarc0-0.2.0-1bl2
  libgcc1-4.9.2-3
  libstdc++6-4.9.2-3
  zlib0-1.2.8-3

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-9-1
  binutils-2.25-1
  cygport-0.18.0.1-1
  gcc-core-4.9.2-3
  gcc-g++-4.9.2-3
  libtool-2.4.6-1
  make-4.1-1

Canonical website:
  http://libarc.sf.net/

Canonical download:
  mirror://sourceforge/libarc/libarc-0.2.0.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack libarc-0.2.0-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./libarc-0.2.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libarc-0.2.0-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libarc-0.2.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libarc0-0.2.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libarc-devel-0.2.0-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(libarc)
  /usr/bin/arcdump.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/libarc.README
  /usr/share/doc/libarc/AUTHORS
  /usr/share/doc/libarc/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/libarc/ChangeLog
  /usr/share/doc/libarc/NEWS
  /usr/share/doc/libarc/README

(libarc0)
  /usr/bin/cygarc-0.dll

(libarc-devel)
  /usr/include/libarc.h
  /usr/lib/libarc.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/libarc.pc

